    <https://wcag.dock.codes/documentation/wcag251/>

  - Local-first software (Ink & Switch)
    <https://www.inkandswitch.com/essay/local-first/>

  - iOS Safari WebGPU / WebAudio / WebMIDI
    <https://webkit.org/blog/17333/webkit-features-in-safari-26-0/>
    <https://www.mattmontag.com/web/unlock-web-audio-in-safari-for-ios-and-macos>
    <https://www.testmuai.com/learning-hub/web-midi-api-browser-support/>

  - Inclusive typography (Atkinson Hyperlegible, OpenDyslexic)
    <https://accessibe.com/blog/knowledgebase/dyslexia-friendly-fonts>

  - VS Code + screen-reader friction (NVDA, JAWS, Emacspeak on terminal)
    <https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/issues/247522>
    <https://github.com/nvaccess/nvda/issues/7605>

  - Voice coding precedent (Talon, Cursorless)
    <https://talon.wiki/Voice%20Coding/voice-coding-overview/>
    <https://handsfreecoding.org/2021/12/12/talon-in-depth-review/>

Every claim above is grounded in one of these sources. Where they disagree, this doc names the disagreement as an open question rather than picking a winner."

